    </teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart" subtype="chapter">
                    <ab><title>Exodus 22</title>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="1">If
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            a thief is found in a den and is smitten, and he dies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            there is no bloodguilt for him.</l>
                        <l n="2">If the sun shines on him,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            there is bloodguilt for him. It is<ref target="#fn1" type="noteAnchor"
                             /> necessary
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            that he pays. And if he has nothing to pay with,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            he shall be sold for his theft.</l>
                        <l n="3">If the theft is
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            found in his hand — from bull to donkey
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            to sheep — alive, he shall pay twice as much.</l>
                        <l n="4"><addSpan spanTo="#add001" />2nd<anchor xml:id="add001" /> If
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            fire breaks out and burns thorns, and
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            stacked or standing grain is consumed, or the field,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            the one who kindled the fire shall pay for the kindling.</l>
                        <l n="5"><addSpan spanTo="#add002" />1st<anchor xml:id="add002" /> If
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            a man causes a field or vineyard to be pastured, and lets
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            his livestock go, and if he pastures in another’s field,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            he shall pay to the injured party of the best of his own field,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            and of the best of his own vineyard.<anchor type="commented"
                                xml:id="seg001" /><ref target="#fn2" type="noteAnchor" /></l>
                        <l n="6">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            If a man gives to another silver or vessels to keep,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            and it is stolen out of the man’s house: if the
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            thief is found, let him pay twice as much.</l>
                        <l n="7">If
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            the thief is not found, the owner of the house shall come near to the judges
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            to show whether he has reached out his hand to another’s property.</l>
                        <milestone unit="page" n="122v" />
                        <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                        <l n="8">For every case of trespass, for a bull, for a donkey,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            for a sheep, for clothing, for any lost thing, of which
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            one says, ‘This is it,’ the words of both of them shall come before the judges.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            And <addSpan spanTo="#add003" /><emph>whom</emph><anchor xml:id="add003"
                             /> the judges convict,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                            he shall pay double to the another.</l>
                        <l n="9">If a man gives to another
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            a donkey or a bull or a sheep or any kind of
                            <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                            livestock to keep, and it dies or is injured or is seized –
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            no one seeing —</l>
                        <l n="10">An oath of the Lord
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            shall be between the of them: whether he has not reached out
                            <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                            his hand to another’s property. And the owner of it shall accept
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            the oath, and he shall not pay.</l>
                        <l n="11">And if
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            it is stolen from him, he shall pay the owner
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            of it.</l>
                        <l n="12">If it is torn, then let him bring
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            it in witness; he shall not pay for the torn one.</l>
                        <l n="13">And if
                            <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                            a man borrows it of another, and it is injured or dies,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            its owner not being with it, he shall pay.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                        <l n="14">If the owner of it is with it, he shall not pay.
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            If it is hired, it came for its hire.</l>
                        <l n="15">And if a man seduces
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            a virgin who is not betrothed, and lies with
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            her, he shall give the dowry for her to be his wife.</l>
                        <l n="16">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            If her father does not want to give her to him for a wife,
                            <milestone unit="page" n="123r" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            he shall measure silver according to the dowry for virgins.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                        <l n="17">You shall not leave a sorceress alive.</l>
                        <l n="18">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            All those who lie with an animal shall be put to death.</l>
                        <l n="19">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            He who sacrifices to devils, except to the Lord only, shall be
                            destroyed.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="5" />
                        <l n="20">You shall not torment a stranger, and you shall not oppress
                            <milestone unit="line" n="6" />
                            him, because you were strangers in the land of Egypt.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="7" />
                        <l n="21">You shall not afflict any widow or orphan.</l>
                        <l n="22">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="8" />
                            If you indeed afflict them, and they cry at all
                            <milestone unit="line" n="9" />
                            to me, I will hear their cry.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="10" />
                        <l n="23">And my anger will burn, and I will kill you
                            <milestone unit="line" n="11" />
                            with a sword, and your wives shall be widows and your children
                            <milestone unit="line" n="12" />
                            orphans.</l>
                        <l n="24">If you lend silver to
                            <milestone unit="line" n="13" />
                            my people, to the poor who is beside you, you shall not be to him
                            <milestone unit="line" n="14" />
                            as a lender, you shall not impose interest on him.</l>
                        <milestone unit="line" n="15" />
                        <l n="25"><addSpan spanTo="#add004" /><emph>If</emph><anchor xml:id="add004"
                             /> you at all take another’s clothing as security,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="16" />
                            you shall return it to him by the time the sun goes down,</l>
                        <l n="26">Because
                            <milestone unit="line" n="17" />
                            that is his only clothing, it is his clothing for his skin. In what
                            <milestone unit="line" n="18" />
                            will he lie down? And it shall be, if he cries to me,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="19" />
                            I will hear, because I am merciful.</l>
                        <l n="27">You shall not curse the judge,
                            <milestone unit="line" n="20" />
                            and you shall not slender the prince among your people.</l>
                        <l n="28">
                            <milestone unit="line" n="21" />
                            You shall not delay to give the heave offering of your grains and of
                            your wine presses.
                            <milestone unit="page" n="123v" />
                            <milestone unit="line" n="1" />
                            You shall give me the firstborn of your sons.</l>
                        <l n="29">Thus shall you do
                            <milestone unit="line" n="2" />
                            to your bulls |and| to your sheep: Seven days it shall be next to its
                            mother. On the eighth
                            <milestone unit="line" n="3" />
                            day you shall give it to me.</l>
                        <l n="30">And you shall be holy men to me. And
                            <milestone unit="line" n="4" />
                            you shall not eat any flesh in the field that is torn. You shall cast it
                            to the dogs.</l>
                    </ab>
                </div>
